'He showed that, scoring two, maybe three depending on the FIFA goal-line decision, and it was important for him and for the team to start well because he is a decisive player for France. Maybe he is our key player and he showed it today.

‘When you play for Real Madrid you have to be a special player. He is still young but he is an excellent player. He has a big talent and for him this competition is the perfect platform to show who he is to everyone.

'This was his first game at the World Cup after being left out four years ago. For all players the World Cup only comes every four years and when you have the chance to play you have to take it.

'You have to enjoy the possibility to play at your best level and do everything for the team. That’s what every player did today.’

